SIMPLE: approver
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Approver
<hw>Ap*prov"er</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who approves. Formerly, one who made proof or trial.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An informer; an accuser.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld> <def>One who confesses a crime and
accuses another. See 1st <er>Approvement</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Approver</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Approver
<hw>Ap*prov"er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See 2d <er>Approve</er>,
<pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld> <def>A bailiff or steward;
an agent.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Jacobs.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Approving</ent>⟦br⟧
